  "response_text": "Here is a comprehensive **Weekly Meal and Fitness Plan** designed for balanced nutrition, sustainable energy, and general fitness improvement. It assumes a goal of **weight maintenance / body recomposition** (building a bit of muscle while losing a little fat) for a moderately active person.\n\n**Important Disclaimer:** Consult a doctor before starting any new diet or exercise program. Adjust portion sizes based on your specific calorie needs, activity level, and hunger cues.\n\n---\n\n### Guiding Principles\n\n- **Hydration:** Drink 2-3 liters of water daily.\n- **Protein:** Aim for 20-30g of protein per meal for satiety and muscle repair.\n- **Whole Foods:** Prioritize vegetables, lean proteins, whole grains, and healthy fats.\n- **Flexibility:** This is a template. Swap days or meals as needed.\n\n---\n\n## The Weekly Meal Plan\n\n### Day 1: Monday (Full Body Strength)\n\n- **Breakfast (7:30 AM):** Greek yogurt (1 cup) with berries (1/2 cup), a tablespoon of chia seeds, and a drizzle of honey.\n- **Lunch (12:30 PM):** Large salad with mixed greens, grilled chicken breast (6 oz), chickpeas (1/2 cup), cucumber, tomatoes, and a light vinaigrette.\n- **Snack (3:30 PM):** Apple slices with 1 tablespoon of almond butter.\n- **Dinner (7:00 PM):** Baked salmon (6 oz) with roasted asparagus and quinoa (1 cup cooked).\n\n### Day 2: Tuesday (Cardio & Core)\n\n- **Breakfast (7:30 AM):** Scrambled eggs (2 whole + 2 whites) with spinach and a slice of whole-wheat toast.\n- **Lunch (12:30 PM):** Turkey and avocado wrap: whole-wheat tortilla, 4 oz turkey, 1/4 avocado, lettuce, tomato, mustard.\n- **Snack (3:30 PM):** Small handful of almonds and a string cheese.\n- **Dinner (7:00 PM):** Lentil soup (2 cups) with a side of mixed greens and a dollop of Greek yogurt.\n\n### Day 3: Wednesday (Upper Body Focus)\n\n- **Breakfast (7:30 AM):** Oatmeal (1/2 cup dry) made with milk, topped with a scoop of protein powder, banana slices, and cinnamon.\n- **Lunch (12:30 PM):** Leftover lentil soup or a tuna salad (canned tuna, light mayo, celery, onion) on a bed of greens.\n- **Snack (3:30 PM):** A pear or a small handful of grapes.\n- **Dinner (7:00 PM):** Lean pork chop (6 oz) with roasted sweet potato wedges and steamed broccoli.\n\n### Day 4: Thursday (Active Recovery / Low Impact)\n\n- **Breakfast (7:30 AM):** Smoothie: 1 cup spinach, 1/2 banana, 1 scoop protein powder, 1 tbsp peanut butter, unsweetened almond milk.\n- **Lunch (12:30 PM):** Quinoa bowl with black beans, corn, diced bell peppers, avocado, and a lime-cilantro dressing.\n- **Snack (3:30 PM):** Cottage cheese (1/2 cup) with a few cherry tomatoes.\n- **Dinner (7:00 PM):** Shrimp stir-fry (6 oz shrimp) with a mix of bell peppers, snap peas, and carrots over brown rice (1/2 cup).\n\n### Day 5: Friday (Lower Body Focus)\n\n- **Breakfast (7:30 AM):** Two-egg veggie omelet (mushrooms, onions, peppers) with 1/2 avocado on the side.\n- **Lunch (12:30 PM):** Leftover shrimp stir-fry or a large chicken Caesar salad (light on dressing, no croutons).\n- **Snack (3:30 PM):** Handful of walnuts and a clementine.\n- **Dinner (7:00 PM):** Lean beef burger (4 oz patty) on a lettuce wrap, with a side of roasted Brussels sprouts.\n\n### Day 6: Saturday (Full Body Strength)\n\n- **Breakfast (9:00 AM):** Protein pancakes (using oats, eggs, banana, and protein powder) with a dollop of Greek yogurt and berries.\n- **Lunch (1:00 PM):** Leftover beef burger and Brussels sprouts, or a large salad with grilled tofu.\n- **Snack (4:00 PM):** Rice cakes (2) with 1 tbsp peanut butter.\n- **Dinner (7:30 PM):** Chicken breast (6 oz) baked with a tomato-based sauce (e.g., salsa or marinara) with a side of zucchini noodles (zoodles).\n\n### Day 7: Sunday (Rest & Prep)\n\n- **Breakfast (9:00 AM):** Whole-grain toast (2 slices) with poached eggs (2) and a side of fruit.\n- **Lunch (1:00 PM):** \"Buddha Bowl\": left over grains + any leftover veggies + a hard-boiled egg or canned salmon.\n- **Snack (4:00 PM):** A piece of fruit or a small dark chocolate square.\n- **Dinner (6:30 PM):** **Meal Prep Dinner:** Roast a whole chicken or a tray of chicken thighs with root vegetables (carrots, potatoes, onions) for the week ahead.\n\n---\n\n## The Weekly Fitness Plan\n\n| Day | Workout Focus | Example Routine (Approx. 45 min) |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Mon** | **Full Body Strength** | **Warm-up:** 5 min jumping jacks, leg swings. <br> **Circuit (3 rounds):** 10 Goblet Squats, 10 Push-ups, 10 Bent-Over Rows (dumbbells), 30-sec Plank. <br> **Cool-down:** Stretch hamstrings, quads, chest. |\n| **Tue** | **Cardio & Core** | **Warm-up:** 5 min brisk walk. <br> **Main:** 25 min moderate jogging, cycling, or swimming. <br> **Core (3 rounds):** 15 Bicycle Crunches, 30-sec Side Plank (each side), 12 Leg Raises. <br> **Cool-down:** Walk 5 min. |\n| **Wed** | **Upper Body** | **Warm-up:** Arm circles, band pull-aparts. <br> **Superset (4 rounds):** <br> A) Dumbbell Bench Press (10 reps) <br> B) Dumbbell Rows (10 reps each arm) <br> **Superset (3 rounds):** <br> C) Overhead Press (10 reps) <br> D) Bicep Curls to Tricep Overhead Extensions (10 reps each). <br> **Cool-down:** Stretch shoulders, triceps. |\n| **Thu",
